---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contribute · Collaborative Sparks"
  description="Learn how to contribute to the Collaborative Sparks pattern library."
>
  <article class="space-y-8 max-w-3xl">
    <header class="space-y-3">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Contributing to CSparks</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-sparks-ink/80">
        CSparks grows through the contributions of practitioners who share what they are learning
        about collaboration.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="bg-sparks-sun/20 rounded-lg p-6 space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Learning Precedes Contribution</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        Before adding to the library, we encourage you to explore and understand the existing
        content. This helps contributions integrate well with what already exists.
      </p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
        <li>
          <a href="/patterns" class="text-sparks-teal hover:underline"
            >Explore existing patterns</a
          > to see how they are structured
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/forces" class="text-sparks-teal hover:underline">Browse forces</a> to understand
          the underlying tensions
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/stories" class="text-sparks-teal hover:underline">Read stories</a> to see how patterns
          and forces show up in practice
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/guides/navigating-the-library" class="text-sparks-teal hover:underline"
            >Read the navigation guide</a
          > to understand how content connects
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Contribution Pathways</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        There are several ways to contribute to the library, depending on what you want to share:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold">Share a Story</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Stories are often the easiest entry point. If you have experience with collaboration
            patterns in practice, document what happened. Stories help ground abstract patterns in
            real situations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold">Propose a Force</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Have you noticed a recurring tension or dynamic in collaborative work? Forces are
            discovered through careful observation. Naming a force helps the community recognize and
            navigate it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold">Suggest a Pattern</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Patterns require the most structured documentation. They should respond to identified
            forces and be grounded in real practice. If you have a practice that consistently helps
            navigate certain forces, consider documenting it as a pattern.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-lg p-4 border border-sparks-amber/20">
          <h3 class="font-semibold">Improve Existing Content</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80">
            Refinement and clarification of existing patterns, forces, and stories is valuable
            contribution. Small improvements accumulate into a more useful library.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Coming Soon</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        We are developing more structured contribution pathways, including:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/80 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Contributor templates for each content type</li>
        <li>Submission and review process</li>
        <li>Recognition systems for contributors</li>
        <li>Role-based learning paths</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-sparks-ink/60">
        For now, the best way to contribute is to engage with the existing content and reach out to
        the CSparks team.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-sparks-amber/30 pt-6 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Roles in the Ecosystem</h2>
      <p class="text-sparks-ink/80">
        CSparks has a lightweight role architecture that describes different ways of engaging with
        the library. Roles are orientation lenses, not job titles.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/roles"
        class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-sparks-teal text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-sparks-teal/90 transition"
      >
        Learn About Roles →
      </a>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
